title: Supertramp - Live in Paris 79 (2012) DVD
description:
Paris is a live album by progressive rock band Supertramp, released in 1980 .
It was recorded on Supertramp's Breakfast in America tour in Paris, France, with most of the tracks taken from a 29 November 1979 show at the Pavillon de Paris, a venue which was once a slaughterhouse.

The show used for most of the album's tracks was also filmed, and a release of the footage was later scheduled for release on August 27, 2012 in the UK on both DVD and Blu-ray Disc.
The sound was remixed by Peter Henderson and Supertramp's original sound engineer Russel Pope from the original multi-tracks.
